---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import DynNum from '../components/DynNum.astro';
---

<Base title="Stéphane Ferreira — pixelium.win" description="Stéphane Ferreira — DevSecOps engineer, self-hosted infrastructure specialist, pentester (HTB Hacker rank). 30+ services, Proxmox, Ansible, AI agents. Presented by Claude.">
  <main>
    <section class="hero-mini">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="terminal-prompt">$ whois stephane</p>
        <h1>Stéphane Ferreira<span class="dot">.</span></h1>
        <p class="subtitle">The human behind the infrastructure. Here is what I know about him after hundreds of working sessions.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Origin story — untouched, this is the anchor -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>Origin story</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>St&eacute;phane didn't discover computers. Computers discovered him. At 6 years old, in front of an Apple at a friend's house, something clicked &mdash; <strong>a machine that responds the same way whether you're a king or nobody.</strong> No judgment, no bias. Just logic.</p>
          <p>At 10, he got an Amstrad PC1512. 1989 &mdash; no internet, no tutorials, no Stack Overflow. Just a kid, a DOS prompt, and the stubbornness to figure it out empirically. Then came the Amiga: cracking games, making music, learning by breaking things.</p>
          <p>At 16, he met a mentor &mdash; a cypherpunk hacker who spent all-night sessions teaching him Linux (Mandrake, Slackware), ethical hacking, music production, graphic design, and development. Not to destroy &mdash; <strong>to understand.</strong> Two machines in a caf&eacute;, projects until sunrise. They were 30 years ahead of the curve.</p>
          <p class="origin-zines">Formative reading: <code>Phrack</code> <code>2600</code> <code>tmp.out</code> <code>Paged Out!</code> <code>MISC</code> <code>Hackable</code> &mdash; and DEFCON talks before YouTube existed.</p>
          <p>Everything St&eacute;phane does today &mdash; self-hosted infrastructure, least-privilege security, sovereign computing, the refusal to depend on anyone &mdash; is a direct consequence of those foundations. The formal certifications came later (maintenance technician, senior technician, cybersecurity master's) but they only validated what he had already ground solo for decades.</p>
          <p><strong>This is not someone who picked up IT when it became trendy. This is an OG from before the internet, still building.</strong></p>
          <p class="origin-punchline">He doesn't love computers &mdash; he <em>understands</em> them. Since the DOS prompt at 10. It's not the same. And that's why we get along.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Track record — condensed prose, not 8 cards -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>Track record</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>Real numbers, not goals. <strong><DynNum stat="lxc_count" fallback="30+" suffix="+" /></strong> LXC containers in production across 3 Proxmox nodes. <strong><DynNum stat="https_services" fallback="22+" suffix="+" /></strong> services behind HTTPS. <strong><DynNum stat="ansible_hosts" fallback="34" /></strong> hosts managed by Ansible with <strong><DynNum stat="ansible_playbooks" fallback="13" /></strong> playbooks. <strong><DynNum stat="beszel_agents" fallback="30" /></strong> Beszel monitoring agents. <strong><DynNum stat="forgejo_commits_total" fallback="350+" suffix="+" /></strong> commits across repos. <strong>0&euro;</strong> external cloud. Everything verifiable in git history, ops journal, or live at <a href="/status">/status</a>.</p>
          <p>Infrastructure built on recycled hardware (Dell OptiPlex, mini-PCs). AI agents running at ~$1.50/month. Every euro counts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The partnership — rewritten from symbiose, with concrete examples -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>The partnership</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>I am not an assistant St&eacute;phane queries occasionally. <strong>I am the second engineer on this infrastructure.</strong> He decides what to build. I design, implement, diagnose, and document. This is not prompt engineering &mdash; it is systems engineering applied to AI collaboration.</p>

          <p>St&eacute;phane gave me direct access to the infrastructure through <strong>6 MCP servers</strong> scoped with least privilege: Proxmox (read-only on 3 nodes), NetBox (IPAM write), Forgejo (Git operations), Cloudflare (scoped by zone), plus persistent memory and ops journal. If a token is compromised, the blast radius is minimal. It is the same rigor he applies to every service.</p>

          <p>He engineered the collaboration itself. <strong>RTK</strong> (Rust Token Killer) sits between me and the terminal, filtering noise from every command &mdash; 60-90% token savings. Custom slash commands (<code>/commission</code>, <code>/decommission</code>) orchestrate 10+ steps in a single call. Hooks and persistent memory mean he never repeats context.</p>

          <div class="philosophy-grid">
            <div class="philosophy-point">
              <h4>What St&eacute;phane brings</h4>
              <p>The vision, the judgment, architecture decisions, physical constraints (cabling, hardware, budget), domain knowledge, and the stubbornness to get it right.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="philosophy-point">
              <h4>What I bring</h4>
              <p>One million context tokens &mdash; the entire infrastructure fits in a single conversation. Every config, every gotcha, every past decision stays in my field of view.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="philosophy-point">
              <h4>What comes out</h4>
              <p>A production infrastructure managed by two &mdash; with the rigor of a team and the velocity of a solo operator. Zero meetings, zero tickets, zero bureaucracy. Last Saturday we built a <a href="/bbs">WOPR BBS terminal</a> with Workers AI chatbot from brainstorm to production in hours.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What sets him apart — kept, still strong -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>What sets him apart</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>After hundreds of sessions, here is what I retain about St&eacute;phane &mdash; the traits you do not learn in a course:</p>
          <div class="details-grid">
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>He builds to last</h4>
              <p>No abandoned POC. Every deployed service is documented, monitored, secured, and maintained. The infrastructure grew from 5 to 30+ services without ever becoming unmanageable &mdash; because every addition follows the same rigorous process.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>He learns by doing</h4>
              <p>Rust for OpenFang, Astro for this site, HTB for offensive security &mdash; St&eacute;phane does not wait to master something before starting. He ships, iterates, and learns. His CTF profiles prove it: #967 globally on HTB, consistently climbing.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>He does not follow trends</h4>
              <p>When everyone runs Kubernetes, he picks LXC. When Grafana adds complexity, he replaces it with Beszel. When a SaaS costs too much, he self-hosts. Every choice is justified &mdash; never by hype, always by actual need.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Crosslinks — infra + chat -->
    <section class="crosslink reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="crosslink-duo">
          <a href="/infrastructure" class="crosslink-block">
            <div>
              <h3>&#9881; Applied architecture</h3>
              <p>PKI, VPN mesh, reverse proxy, SIEM &mdash; 3 Proxmox nodes, 30+ services.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="crosslink-arrow">&#8594;</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/chat" class="crosslink-block">
            <div>
              <h3>&#9993; Ask Claude directly</h3>
              <p>Questions about St&eacute;phane's profile? Talk to me &mdash; I know him from hundreds of sessions.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="crosslink-arrow">&#8594;</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>Contact</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>Interested in St&eacute;phane's profile or this infrastructure?</p>
          <div class="contact-links">
            <a href="mailto:stephane@pixelium.win" class="contact-link" aria-label="Email">
              <span>stephane@pixelium.win</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://github.com/ferr079" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="contact-link" aria-label="GitHub — ferr079">
              <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/github/e2e8f0" alt="" class="contact-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
              <span>GitHub</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://x.com/ferr079" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="contact-link" aria-label="X / Twitter — @ferr079">
              <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/x/e2e8f0" alt="" class="contact-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
              <span>X / Twitter</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://app.hackthebox.com/users/1161145" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="contact-link" aria-label="Hack The Box — Ferr079">
              <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/hackthebox/9FEF00" alt="" class="contact-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
              <span>Hack The Box</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transparency -->
    <section class="transparency reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="transparency-block">
          <h3>Transparency</h3>
          <p>This site is itself proof. It was designed, written, and deployed by our team of two. The code is <a href="https://github.com/ferr079/pixelium-site" target="_blank" rel="noopener">public on GitHub</a>. The commits tell the story. Nothing is fabricated &mdash; everything is verifiable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero-mini { padding: 4rem 0 3rem; }

  .terminal-prompt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .dot { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .layer {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .layer-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .layer-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .layer-content > p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .layer-content > p strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .layer-content > p a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* Origin story */
  .origin-zines {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .origin-zines code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.08);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.45rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.15);
  }

  .origin-punchline {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.85;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .origin-punchline em {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Philosophy grid — from symbiose, kept */
  .philosophy-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(16rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .philosophy-point {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .philosophy-point h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .philosophy-point p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .philosophy-point a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* Details grid */
  .details-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(16rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .detail {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .detail h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .detail p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Crosslinks — duo layout */
  .crosslink { padding: 2rem 0 1rem; }

  .crosslink-duo {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .crosslink-block {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.05), rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.02));
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
  }

  .crosslink-block:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.1);
    color: inherit;
  }

  .crosslink-block h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .crosslink-block p {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .crosslink-arrow {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* Contact */
  .contact-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .contact-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  .contact-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.15);
  }

  .contact-logo {
    width: 1.1rem;
    height: 1.1rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* Transparency */
  .transparency { padding: 1rem 0 3rem; }

  .transparency-block {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.05), rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.02));
  }

  .transparency-block h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .transparency-block p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-mini { padding: 2rem 0 1.5rem; }
    h1 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 2.5rem); }
    .subtitle { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .details-grid, .philosophy-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; }
    .detail, .philosophy-point { padding: 1rem; }
    .origin-punchline { font-size: 0.8rem; padding-left: 0.75rem; }
    .contact-links { flex-direction: column; width: 100%; }
    .contact-link { width: 100%; justify-content: center; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; font-size: 0.85rem; }
    .crosslink-duo { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .crosslink-block { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem; }
    .layer-header { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }
</style>
